This paper deals with transfer learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new transfer learning method that utilizes both source-target similarities and inter-source relationships, which suggests that it could fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with pool-based active learning, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions experiments on real-world datasets, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
